# Docker build context is the repo root (the peer image's `context: ..`). Keep it lean: exclude build
# outputs, caches, and VCS so a change to any of them doesn't bust the peer builder's cache — and so the
# self-build path never ingests a host's foreign-arch/OS gradle state (macOS klibs, Konan outputs, etc.).
# The prebuilt path's binary lives under webrtc-harness-endpoint/build/bin — re-included below.
.git
.gradle
**/build
!webrtc-harness-endpoint/build/bin/**
.kotlin
**/.kotlin
kotlin-js-store
build-logic/build
**/*.klib
.idea
.vscode
*.log
